# Commit Message Template for enrich-ddf-floor-2
#
# Format: <type>(<scope>): <subject>
#
# Types:
#   feat:     New feature or enhancement
#   fix:      Bug fix
#   docs:     Documentation changes
#   style:    Code style changes (formatting, etc)
#   refactor: Code refactoring without feature changes
#   test:     Adding or updating tests
#   chore:    Maintenance tasks, dependencies
#   perf:     Performance improvements
#   ci:       CI/CD pipeline changes
#   build:    Build system or external dependencies
#   revert:   Revert a previous commit
#
# Scope examples:
#   api, frontend, database, enrichment, integrations
#   hunter, clearbit, pdl, apollo, zerobounce
#   tests, docs, config, deployment
#
# Examples:
#   feat(enrichment): add real-time person data enrichment via Hunter.io
#   fix(frontend): resolve TypeScript compilation errors in Components
#   feat(integrations): implement Clearbit company enrichment API
#   test(e2e): add comprehensive data enrichment flow tests
#   docs(api): update API documentation with new enrichment endpoints
#   chore(deps): update React and Vite to latest versions
#   fix(database): resolve SQLite connection pooling issues
#   feat(api): add quota management for external API calls
#
# Guidelines:
#   - Use imperative mood ("add" not "added" or "adds")
#   - Keep subject line under 50 characters
#   - Capitalize the subject line
#   - Do not end subject line with a period
#   - Use body to explain what and why, not how
#   - Reference issues with "Fixes #123" or "Closes #123"
#   - Break lines at 72 characters in the body
#
# Body (optional - explain what and why):
# 
# 
# Footer (optional - reference issues):
# Fixes #123
# Closes #456
